content.description: Overhanging climbing past the first bolt tosses you right into the first crux and will provide a nice pump for the rest of the route. Thought provoking moves above will insure a good pump for the grade. As with many Canyon routes completing the pitch seems to be the crux.
content.protection: Seven Bolts & Open Cold Shut Anchors   Stick Clip First Bolt
content.location: This route is the third bolted route from the left on the west end of the Can. There is small pillar below the start of the route.

content.description: Crunchy start leads to a relentless face out a small roof. Bouldery!

A unique route that follows a beautiful right facing dihedral. Stemming, jamming and pulling pockets with many possible combinations. Great warmup, on steep rock, with early morning sun, excellent movement with confidence inspiring bolt spacing. It's all good.
content.protection: Eight Bolts for protection with open cold shuts at the anchor.
content.location: This route climbs the right facing dihedral near the west end (left side) of "The Can" (second bolted route from the left).

content.description: This is an excellent route with bouldery moves on monos, two finger pockets, and crimps. After the boulder problem enjoy some sweet dihedral climbing that might keep you pretty gripped to the open shuts. Some of the nicest blonde stone around!
content.location: this route is the furthest right route at The Can. It is on a seperate clean blonde face slightly uphill to the right of the main Can routes.(the route to its left is Money Shot 12a)

content.description: Short, Hard & Painful but worth doing at least once.
content.protection: Four Bolts & Open cold Shut Anchors
content.location: This route is the leftmost (West) of all the routes on The Can. Located on a small butress just left of a right facing dihedral (Morning Torque).

content.description: Fun bottom leads to one of the best upper sections in the canyon.  Climb upper flake to the top.
content.location: Just to the left of Courtesy Flush.

content.description: Good pockets and moves stop at the first anchors
content.location: After hiking from the parking turn left ont trail and walk 11-12 minutes the climb is a short climb to the left of a big crack

content.description: Start with first four bolts of Courtesy Flush, then clip at the anchor and merge left onto upper line of bolts on Drip Dry. After a small roof follow the flake to the anchor.
content.location: Located on right side of the Can area.

content.description: The Wall is pretty much all yellow wall connected to a buttress with three roofs.
